window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>In a false city built on lies, the factions prepare for war.</b></p> <p>The orcs awaken primeval curses. The cultists collect on ancient debts. The goblins fuel their war rigs.</p> <p>None of it will be enough for what’s coming.</p> <p>After the Golden Door incident, Lucas and Hugo have never been in more danger. Their allies are gone, the gods want them dead, and their new patron who caused all of these problems is more of a hindrance than a benefactor.</p> <p>But the Climb must continue.</p> <p>The pair descend into the Strand, a gothic city on the brink of tearing itself apart. By day, its citizens worry about dodging goblin artillery or being extorted by orc gangsters. But by night, the spirits grow restless. Amongst the chaos, a rogue necromancer plots their revenge.</p> <p>With little time left, Lucas and Hugo will have to fight every step of the way for answers.</p> <p>But secrets get buried for a reason, and no one will be prepared for the consequences.</p> <p>Dive into a LitRPG apocalypse story with classes, skills, monster waves, and a progression system full of secrets and possibilities. Perfect for fans of Rogue Ascension, Defiance of the Fall, and The Primal Hunter!</p> <p>First on Royal Road with over half a million views, now professionally edited and soon to be available on Amazon and Audible narrated by Jonathan Waters. Buy a copy!</p>"; 
